ci_support_linux_64_.yaml:
cdt_name:
- conda
channel_sources:
- conda-forge
channel_targets:
- conda-forge main
docker_image:
- quay.io/condaforge/linux-anvil-x86_64:alma9
python_min:
- '3.9'

about.description:
Properties are a very useful feature of Python, effectively allowing
an attribute to masquerade as a method (with no arguments other than
self). However, sometimes we want to store the results of an expensive
computation in an attribute.
about.summary: A package for making properties lazy

name: lazy-property
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "lazy-property" %}
{% set version = "0.0.1" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.org/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 3a1cd36949b323468731ba569e169415a609d5904d53fffe982055fbe67b1180

build:
  number: 1
  noarch: python
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv

requirements:
  host:
    - pip
    - python {{ python_min }}
    - setuptools
  run:
    - python >={{ python_min }}

test:
  imports:
    - lazy_property
  commands:
    - pip check
  requires:
    - pip
    - python {{ python_min }}

about:
  home: https://github.com/jackmaney/lazy-property
  license: MIT
  license_family: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: 'A package for making properties lazy'

  description: |
    Properties are a very useful feature of Python, effectively allowing 
    an attribute to masquerade as a method (with no arguments other than 
    self). However, sometimes we want to store the results of an expensive 
    computation in an attribute. 
  doc_url: https://github.com/jackmaney/lazy-property
  dev_url: https://github.com/jackmaney/lazy-property

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - jan-janssen
